\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is the official user guide for version 0.2 of the hostmap host name
 discovery tool.
 This guide is designed to explain what hostmap is, how it works, and what
 you can do with it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The latetest version of this document can be found on the hostmap web site:
 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

http://hostmap.sourceforge.net
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The hostmap host name discovery tool is an utility designed to discover
 the host names related to a given IP address.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The primary users of hostmap are professionals performing vulnerability
 assessments and penetration tests.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Requirements
\end_layout

