\begin_layout Subsection
Use case
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the real world an IP address can be registered in a DNS server with multiple
 host names, because it can have some aliases or it is hosting a bunch of
 websites.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example the IP address 1.2.3.4 can has the following names registered,
 as you can see from a piece of the BIND zone configuration file:
\end_layout

